chart.name: Modified - Disk Metrics 24h Growth %
chart.programText:
# A = data('Disk*', filter=filter('namespace', 'AWS/EC2') and filter('InstanceId', '*') and filter('stat', 'sum'), rollup='rate', extrapolation='last_value', maxExtrapolations=5).sum(by=['sf_metric']).scale(60).mean(over='1h').publish(label='A', enable=False)
# B = (A).timeshift('1d').publish(label='B', enable=False)
# C = (A/B-1).scale(100).publish(label='C')

CW_DWOPS = data('DiskWriteOps', filter=filter('stat', 'sum') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/EC2') and filter('InstanceId', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='CW_DWOPS', enable=False)
OTEL_DWOPS = data('system.disk.ops', filter=filter('direction', 'write') and filter('cloud_provider', 'aws') and filter('cloud_infrastructure_service', 'EC2') and filter('host_id', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='OTEL_DWOPS', enable=False)
#fill should be fill(count=5)
VIRTUAL_DWOPS = combine(CW_DWOPS if OTEL_DWOPS is None else OTEL_DWOPS).fill().sum().scale(60).mean(over='1h').publish(label="VIRTUAL_DWOPS", enable=False)
DWOPS_TSHIFT = (VIRTUAL_DWOPS).timeshift('1d').publish(label='DWOPS_TSHIFT', enable=False)
DWOPS = (VIRTUAL_DWOPS/DWOPS_TSHIFT-1).scale(100).publish(label='DWOPS')

CW_DROPS = data('DiskReadOps', filter=filter('stat', 'sum') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/EC2') and filter('InstanceId', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='CW_DROPS', enable=False)
OTEL_DROPS = data('system.disk.ops', filter=filter('direction', 'read') and filter('cloud_provider', 'aws') and filter('cloud_infrastructure_service', 'EC2') and filter('host_id', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='OTEL_DROPS', enable=False)
#fill should be fill(count=5)
VIRTUAL_DROPS = combine(CW_DROPS if OTEL_DROPS is None else OTEL_DROPS).fill().sum().scale(60).mean(over='1h').publish(label="VIRTUAL_DROPS", enable=False)
DROPS_TSHIFT = (VIRTUAL_DROPS).timeshift('1d').publish(label='DWOPS_TSHIFT', enable=False)
DROPS = (VIRTUAL_DROPS/DROPS_TSHIFT-1).scale(100).publish(label='DROPS')

CW_DWIO = data('DiskWriteBytes', filter=filter('stat', 'sum') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/EC2') and filter('InstanceId', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='CW_DWIO', enable=False)
OTEL_DWIO = data('system.disk.io', filter=filter('direction', 'write') and filter('cloud_provider', 'aws') and filter('cloud_infrastructure_service', 'EC2') and filter('host_id', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='OTEL_DWIO', enable=False)
#fill should be fill(count=5)
VIRTUAL_DWIO = combine(CW_DWIO if OTEL_DWIO is None else OTEL_DWIO).fill().sum().scale(60).mean(over='1h').publish(label="VIRTUAL_DWIO", enable=False)
DWIO_TSHIFT = (VIRTUAL_DWIO).timeshift('1d').publish(label='DWIO_TSHIFT', enable=False)
DWIO = (VIRTUAL_DWIO/DWIO_TSHIFT-1).scale(100).publish(label='DWIO')

CW_DRIO = data('DiskReadBytes', filter=filter('stat', 'sum') and filter('namespace', 'AWS/EC2') and filter('InstanceId', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='CW_DRIO', enable=False)
OTEL_DRIO = data('system.disk.io', filter=filter('direction', 'read') and filter('cloud_provider', 'aws') and filter('cloud_infrastructure_service', 'EC2') and filter('host_id', '*')).mean(by=['AWSUniqueId']).publish(label='OTEL_DRIO', enable=False)
#fill should be fill(count=5)
VIRTUAL_DRIO = combine(CW_DRIO if OTEL_DRIO is None else OTEL_DRIO).fill().sum().scale(60).mean(over='1h').publish(label="VIRTUAL_DRIO", enable=False)
DRIO_TSHIFT = (VIRTUAL_DRIO).timeshift('1d').publish(label='DRIO_TSHIFT', enable=False)
DRIO = (VIRTUAL_DRIO/DRIO_TSHIFT-1).scale(100).publish(label='DRIO')
